The paper deals with sparsification of matrices, which is a topic that falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS). The use of iteratively resampling rows involves techniques from information theory (cs.IT) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper also discusses the theoretical guarantees of the sparsification scheme, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and optimization (cs.SI).
